{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QuSqebCdQHyYdTKN7qXVky","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now let me create a comprehensive summary with all the findings:\n\n## Visual Testing Setup - Complete Report\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the RNG Utopia platform's visual testing infrastructure. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **`pnpm test:visual` Configuration**\n\n**Root package.json** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/package.json`):\n```json\n\"test:visual\": \"turbo run test:visual\"\n```\n\n**Apps/platform package.json** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/package.json`):\n```json\n\"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n\"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\"\n```\n\n**Turbo config** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/turbo.json`):\n```json\n\"test:visual\": {\n  \"cache\": false\n}\n```\n\nThe `pnpm test:visual` command runs through Turbo which delegates to the platform app's Playwright test runner. Caching is disabled for visual tests to ensure fresh comparisons.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Playwright Configuration**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n\nKey settings:\n- **Test directory**: `./e2e`\n- **Snapshot template**: `{testDir}/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}`\n- **Max diff pixel ratio**: `0.015` (1.5% tolerance for pixel differences)\n- **Base URL**: `http://localhost:3000`\n- **Viewport**: 1280x1080\n- **Browser**: Chromium (Desktop Chrome)\n- **Screenshots**: Off by default; enabled via `toHaveScreenshot()` calls\n- **Traces**: Off by default\n- **Parallel execution**: `fullyParallel: true`\n- **Workers**: 1 worker (serialized execution)\n- **Retries**: 0\n\n**Automatic dev server**:\n```typescript\nwebServer: {\n  command: \"pnpm dev\",\n  url: \"http://localhost:3000\",\n  reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,\n  timeout: 30_000,\n}\n```\n\nThis means **no manual dev server is needed** — Playwright automatically launches `pnpm dev` before running tests and reuses it if already running (unless in CI).\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Visual Regression Baselines/Snapshots Storage**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/`\n\nStructure:\n```\ne2e/__snapshots__/\n├── visual/routes.spec.ts/       # Route baseline snapshots\n├── visual/states.spec.ts/       # State variant snapshots\n```\n\n**Baseline files** (17 PNG files total):\n- **Routes** (12 files): home.png, coinflip.png, lord-of-rngs.png, close-call.png, crash.png, game-of-trades.png, profile.png, quests.png, loot.png, fairness.png, leaderboard.png, 404.png\n- **States** (5 files): home-disconnected.png, home-connected.png, profile-connected.png, coinflip-disconnected.png, coinflip-connected.png\n\nTo update baselines:\n```bash\npnpm test:visual:update\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Existing Visual Test Files**\n\n**Directory**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/`\n\n**Test files**:\n\n1. **Fixtures** (`e2e/fixtures.ts`) — Custom `stablePage` fixture extending Playwright's `test`:\n   - Seeds `Math.random()` with Mulberry32 (seed=42) for deterministic randomness\n   - Freezes `Date.now()` to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n   - Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for deterministic keypair generation\n   - Disables CSS animations/transitions and pauses SVG SMIL animations\n   - Waits for document fonts and network idle after navigation\n   - Collects and fails on console errors\n\n2. **Routes** (`e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`) — 12 route baseline tests:\n   - Tests each route in default state (disconnected wallet)\n   - Uses `fullPage: true` for complete page screenshots\n   - Routes: home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs, close-call, crash, game-of-trades, profile, quests, loot, fairness, leaderboard, 404\n\n3. **States** (`e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`) — 5 state variant tests:\n   - Tests wallet connection/disconnection states\n   - Home page: